text:
So, I'm kind of a lurker, 'cuz I have no sense of time, so I watch the archives... but I heard you say that there might be a chance of you playing a Touhou game on stream, so I have to be that guy and say... yes, please XD
The series became very important to me, so I'd like to give a liiiiitle push to see if it can happen. Also, maybe a little info so you can choose which one. Thing is, even though all games have the same general mechanics (move, shoot, bomb, hold down the left shift key to move slowly/use the alt shot-type), each game has its own mechanic. Like Th18 has money, so you can buy a skill or attack at the end of each stage, 16 has a secondary shot-type that is powered up separatedly from the main one, etc. My advice would be Th17, though. In that one, some enemies drop a special item when killed, and when you pick it up, it gets stored on a side bar. Pick 5 items to fill the bar, and you enter a super mode, depending on what you picked (3 wolves = forward attack, 3 eagles = spread attack, 3 otters = orbitals that block bullets, just points if none of those), so it makes the player feel very powerful. You can play any Touhou game for any reason, like you know a song, or for certain character, or it looks more interesting, etc, and I'll be happy either way XD

text: Regarding the Di**ey World stream, I don't think it's about nerd or cringe or whatever. People were just caught off guard when you went from 0 to 100 in a matter of seconds and kept going strong throughout the entire stream. In my opinion, the way you got invested into this is what I think is the whole point of these theme parks (ignoring the money aspect). People are meant to get invested in them, get lost in their magic, get excited about all the fun things you can do and see. Seeing you get balls to the wall hyped over everything was incredibly adorable and is just a part of you being you. People trying to make it look like it's something bad most likely just don't have something they can get this excited about and as a result trying to take the fun from everyone else as well.
